The TDCI joined two training sessions at the Asia-Pacific Transport Forum in Manila.

In "Monitoring Progress of the UN Decade of Sustainable Transport," TDC presented the importance of open, high-quality, and accessible data to enable monitoring of the UN Decade. Participants discussed how systematic progress monitoring can identify what is working, where challenges persist, and how countries can strengthen implementation.

In "Using Transport Data for Better Investment Decisions," TDCI presented alongside the Asian Transport Observatory (ATO), the World Bank's ieCONNECT platform, and other regional initiatives, exploring how transport data platforms support better infrastructure and policy decisions across Asia and the Pacific.
